# 2026-03-17 (cont. 14 — MOD=01, MOD=10, MOD=00 R/M=110, word memory read)

Completed all displacement modes in ParseModRMByte and wired up word-width memory reads in DecodeSource.

## What Was Built

* Decoder.cs — ParseModRMByte signature widened from single byte to `byte[] instructions` so it can read displacement bytes from the instruction stream.
* Decoder.cs — MOD=01 branch: 8-bit displacement via `(sbyte)instructions[2]`, implicit widening to `short` handles sign extension.
* Decoder.cs — MOD=10 branch: 16-bit displacement via `(short)(instructions[2] | (instructions[3] << 8))`, same OR-shift little-endian reassembly as word immediates.
* Decoder.cs — MOD=00 R/M=110 special case: direct address — null base, null index, 16-bit displacement from instruction stream. `_transRM[6]` (BP, null) remains correct for MOD=01/10.
* Decoder.cs — flattened nesting: removed else block, all four mode returns are now early-exit ifs. Stale comments removed.
* Cpu.cs — DecodeSource word-width memory read: resolve EA once into `addr`, read two bytes `(ushort)(Mem.ReadByte(addr) | Mem.ReadByte((ushort)(addr + 1)) << 8)`.
* DecoderTests.cs — 3 new tests: Decode_0x00_ModRM_Mod01_BxSi_Displacement8, Decode_0x00_ModRM_Mod10_BxSi_Displacement16, Decode_0x00_ModRM_Mod00_RM110_DirectAddress.
* CpuTests.cs — 1 new test: Execute_AddAxMemBx_WordFromMemory (0x1000 + [0x1234] = 0x2234).
* CLAUDE.md — new "Sign Extension via Signed Cast" section, updated development state (31→33 green, MOD=01/10 done), removed stale decoder test gotcha.

## Key Decisions

+ ParseModRMByte takes the whole instructions array — cleanest way to give it access to displacement bytes without a separate pass-back-and-read-later dance.
+ `(sbyte)byteValue` for sign extension — C# type system does two's complement reinterpretation and implicit widening to `short`. No manual bit flipping needed. Documented in CLAUDE.md for reuse in relative jumps and 0x83 group.
+ MOD=00 R/M=110 handled as explicit special case (`mode == 0b00 && rm == 0b110`) rather than modifying `_transRM[6]` — keeps the table correct for MOD=01/10 where R/M=110 really does mean BP.
+ Redundant `(short)` cast dropped from sign extension — Roslyn IDE0370, `(sbyte)` implicitly widens to `short`.
+ xUnit `Assert.NotNull` has `[NotNull]` — `!` null-forgiving operators after it are redundant (IDE0370). Stripped from decoder tests.

## Status

* 33 of 34 tests green. 1 integration test (Opcode00Tests) skipped.

## Resolved

+ MOD=01 8-bit displacement — sign-extended via `(sbyte)` cast.
+ MOD=10 16-bit displacement — OR-shift little-endian reassembly.
+ MOD=00 R/M=110 special case — direct address, no base/index.
+ Word-width memory read in DecodeSource — two-byte read with OR-shift.
+ Where displacement reading belongs — ParseModRMByte, with full instructions array passed in.

## Open

? Memory as destination — write path (`ADD [BX], AL`) requires WriteByte after execute. Direction bit + MemoryOperand interaction.
? ByteLength is currently `instructions.Length` — not computed by the decoder from opcode + format + mod.
? Opcode00 integration test unskip — once full ADD pipeline handles all addressing modes.

